definition:
A man of the tribe of Judah living at the time of Divided Monarchy, only mentioned at 1Ch.3.24; 
 son of: Elioenai (H0454B); 
 brother of: Eliashib (H0475), Pelaiah (H6411B), Akkub (H6126), Johanan (H3110I), Delaiah (H1806) and Anani (H6054)
Another name of ho.dav.yah (הוֹדַוְיָה "Hodaviah" H1938G) 
 § Hodaiah = "praise ye Jehovah"
 son of the royal line of Judah
